Interface GenericToolsInterface

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    ConfigurableToolsInterface, EngineInterface, SimpleToolsInterface
    All Known Implementing Classes:

    • Method Detail

      • reset

        void reset()
        Reset or clear any cached information in the underlying tool or service. The implementation should be able to recognize if the underlying tool or service is not actually running. If the tool is not running, then this should exit gracefully without adversely affecting anything.

      • shutdown

        void shutdown()
        Shutdown the underlying tool or service. The implementation should be able to recognize if the underlying tool or service is not actually running. If the tool is not running, then this should exit gracefully without adversely affecting anything.

      • isToolRunning

        boolean isToolRunning()
        TRUE if the underlying tool is running. Typically called AFTER initialization attempts have been made.

      • getCoreInterface

        CoreInterface getCoreInterface()
                        throws java.lang.IllegalStateException
        Retrieve the instance of the CoreInterface used to communicate with the framework.
        Returns:
        CoreInterface instance.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - if the CoreInterface is null, has not been initialized yet, or is otherwise invalid.
